This article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on July 19, 2019, commemorating the 50th anniversary of the Apollo 11 lunar landing. The proclamation honors the brave astronauts of the Apollo 11 mission, including Neil Armstrong, Buzz Aldrin, and Michael Collins, and acknowledges the sacrifices, dedication, and talent of all those involved in the mission. The article highlights the significance of the lunar landing in advancing science, technology, and commerce, and emphasizes the importance of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) and the aerospace industry in the nation's pursuit of greatness and defense. President Trump reaffirms his commitment to human space exploration and the goal of returning Americans to the Moon and eventually sending them to Mars. The proclamation also calls upon public officials, educators, and all Americans to honor the Apollo 11 mission and those who have served in the nation's space program.